##### Component Validation Best Practices
**CRITICAL: Avoid these common validation errors:**

**For comprehensive client library guidelines, see the "AEM Client Library Guidelines" section below.**

1. **Component Definition File**
   - ‚úÖ **ALWAYS use `.content.xml`** for component definitions
   - ‚ùå **NEVER use `.properties`** files for component definitions
   - ‚úÖ **Required structure**:
     ```xml
     <?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
     <jcr:root xmlns:cq="http://www.day.com/jcr/cq/1.0" xmlns:jcr="http://www.jcp.org/jcr/1.0"
         jcr:primaryType="cq:Component"
         jcr:title="Component Title"
         jcr:description="Component description"
         componentGroup="My Site - Content"/>
     ```

2. **Edit Configuration**
   - ‚úÖ **Use simple edit configurations** following existing project patterns
   - ‚ùå **Avoid complex edit configs** with empty nodes and handlers
   - ‚úÖ **Recommended structure**:
     ```xml
     <?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
     <jcr:root xmlns:cq="http://www.day.com/jcr/cq/1.0" xmlns:jcr="http://www.jcp.org/jcr/1.0"
         cq:inherit="{Boolean}true"
         jcr:primaryType="cq:EditConfig"/>
     ```

3. **HTL Template Validation**
   - ‚úÖ **Use explicit context** for style attributes: `${variable @ context='unsafe'}`
   - ‚ùå **Avoid direct variable usage** in style attributes without context
   - ‚úÖ **Example**: `style="background-image: url('${imagePath @ context='unsafe'}')`

4. **Sling Model Dependencies**
   - ‚úÖ **Only use available dependencies** from the project's POM
   - ‚ùå **Avoid core components interfaces** if not available
   - ‚úÖ **Check existing models** for dependency patterns
   - ‚úÖ **Use simple @Model annotation** for basic components

5. **Client Library Structure**
   - ‚úÖ **Always include `.content.xml`** for client library configuration
   - ‚úÖ **Use proper categories** and dependencies
   - ‚úÖ **Include manifest files** (css.txt, js.txt)

